# Component Standards (MANDATORY)

## UI Library Standards (MANDATORY)
You MUST use ONLY these approved libraries:
- **Components**: shadcn/ui components exclusively - NO custom UI components without justification
- **Icons**: Lucide React icons strictly - NO other icon libraries or custom SVGs
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS with design tokens only - NO custom CSS or inline styles

```typescript
// REQUIRED: shadcn/ui + Lucide React pattern
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button'
import { Card, CardContent, CardHeader } from '@/components/ui/card'
import { Badge } from '@/components/ui/badge'
import { CheckCircle, XCircle } from 'lucide-react'

<Card className="bg-card border-border">
  <CardHeader>
    <CheckCircle className="w-5 h-5 text-green-500" />
    <Badge variant="secondary">Intermediate</Badge>
  </CardHeader>
  <CardContent>
    <Button variant="default" size="md">Submit</Button>
  </CardContent>
</Card>

// FORBIDDEN: Custom components or non-Lucide icons
import { CustomButton } from './custom-button'
import { MdCheck } from 'react-icons/md'
```

## Reusability Requirements
You MUST create components that work across multiple pages:
- **PageLayout**: MUST work on ALL 6 pages (100% reusability)
- **ActionButtons**: MUST work on Practice/Reading/Conversation (75% reusability)
  - Practice: Submit/Hint/Skip buttons
  - Reading: Continue/Bookmark/Translate buttons  
  - Conversation: Send/Save/Continue buttons
- **SessionStats**: MUST work on all metric pages (85% reusability)

## Button Specifications
```typescript
